		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Diwali</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about the Indian holiday.  For the dancehall instrumental, see <a href="/wiki/Diwali_Riddim" title="Diwali Riddim">Diwali Riddim</a> .</div>
<table class="infobox" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; background-color: orange">
<center>Diwali</center>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="/wiki/File:Diwali_Diya.jpg" class="image" title="Diwali"><img alt="Diwali" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Diwali_Diya.jpg/250px-Diwali_Diya.jpg" width="250" height="188" border="0" /></a><br />
<span style="">A row of lamps, part of the Diwali observance.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Also called</th>
<td class="" style="">Translation: Row of Lights; Deepavali, Festival of Lights</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Observed by</th>
<td class="" style="">Religiously by <a href="/wiki/Hindu" title="Hindu" class="mw-redirect">Hindus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sikh" title="Sikh">Sikhs</a>, <a href="/wiki/Buddhist" title="Buddhist" class="mw-redirect">Buddhists</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jain" title="Jain" class="mw-redirect">Jains</a>. Other Indians celebrate the cultural aspects.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
